peopleAlsoAsk.question: Does China have 2 capitals?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet:
There are traditionally four major historical capitals of China referred to as
the 'Four Great Ancient Capitals of China' (simplified Chinese: 中国四大古都;
traditional Chinese: 中國四大古都; pinyin: Zhōngguó Sì Dà Gǔ Dū). The four are
Beijing, Nanjing, Luoyang and Xi"an (Chang"an).

peopleAlsoAsk.question: Why China changed its capital?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet:
Once in charge, it wasn't uncommon for a new emperor to shift the imperial
capital in order to: Rebuild after a great loss, as in the Han era when Liu Bang
moved the capital from Xianyang to nearby Chang'an (now Xi'an), after the former
was destroyed during a rebellion.
